{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_tcfVdg4hkegJMZSnM3YgBB6Y","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: write_data\n3\toutput:\n4\t  tables: array\n5\t  rows: number\n6\t  ok: boolean\n7\tdependsOn: [read_sources]\n8\trole: general\n9\tfunctions: []\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tWrite the complete source-derived data model into the LIVE project. `query` and `read_sources` are\n13\tin scope. Use `writeProjectTable(name, schema, rows)` for every table so each matching source record\n14\tlands as a row at creation; never create an empty table when the source has matching data. Include the\n15\tsource's identifiers, contacts, dates, payments, stated totals, and attribution. This is a bounded\n16\twrite node: do not write pages or APIs here and do not rely on a value declared by an earlier model\n17\tstatement. Emit exactly one self-contained statement that performs all table writes and resolves the\n18\tnames and row count. Statement-local variables disappear after execution, so do not declare `writes`\n19\tin one statement and resolve it in another. Do not use an IIFE: place the synchronous writer calls\n20\tdirectly inside the resolved object:\n21\t\n22\t```typescript\n23\tcurrentTask.resolve({\n24\t  tables: ['<matching table name>'],\n25\t  rows: <source-derived row count>,\n26\t  ok: [\n27\t    writeProjectTable('<source-derived table>', { title: '<title>', description: '<description>', columns: { id: { type: 'string', description: 'Primary key', primaryKey: true, generated: 'uuid' } } }, [/* source-derived rows */]),\n28\t  ].every((write) => write.ok),\n29\t});\n30\t```"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_VS8SpQtfQDSL4mOWXxONhNyp","session_id":"a5bdaf5f-36c3-4bd0-a7f1-82b85daace12","uuid":"d9225cdd-b08e-4718-b3ae-ce972aeb193b","timestamp":"2026-07-16T09:08:02.991Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace app build completion"}
