{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_l14RhBslP6U1P6dEC2Z1coCp","type":"tool_result","content":"<persisted-output>\nOutput too large (7.7MB). Full output saved to: /home/vasilis/.claude/projects/-home-vasilis-LMTHING-lmthing/a5bdaf5f-36c3-4bd0-a7f1-82b85daace12/tool-results/bna4fzqco.txt\n\nPreview (first 2KB):\n1:[{\"seq\":1,\"event\":{\"ts\":1784192122881,\"type\":\"user_message\",\"nodeId\":\"491d03a7-5a9a-4d6f-b7fc-f63612789864\",\"content\":\"Ok this is getting out of hand. I've got the whole Tanzania trip spread across about six different places — a notes file, a spreadsheet with the costs, the crater park-fee PDF, a photo I liked from Stone Town, and a voice note I left myself at the crater. Attaching all of it. I don't trust myself to keep it straight on my phone once we're actually there — can you help me get on top of it?\",\"attachments\":[{\"kind\":\"file\",\"url\":\"/api/uploads/6b5128a0-fb1f-47db-b283-1c6a36b166e9\",\"mediaType\":\"text/markdown\",\"filename\":\"tanzaniamemories.md\"},{\"kind\":\"file\",\"url\":\"/api/uploads/b18c3244-0f47-4e51-b614-ac7099e75646\",\"mediaType\":\"application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet\",\"filename\":\"trip-costs.xlsx\"},{\"kind\":\"file\",\"url\":\"/api/uploads/96874343-0a87-495c-884f-228061b3465f\",\"mediaType\":\"application/pdf\",\"filename\":\"ngorongoro-conservation-area-tariffs.pdf\"},{\"kind\":\"image\",\"url\":\"/api/uploads/d0a218fb-0d32-483d-8d50-d1cdcfaaff96\",\"mediaType\":\"image/jpeg\",\"filename\":\"stone-town-zanzibar.jpg\"},{\"kind\":\"audio\",\"url\":\"/api/uploads/e655af50-0405-46c2-bbf6-2d1497bb586f\",\"mediaType\":\"audio/mpeg\",\"filename\":\"voice-memo.mp3\",\"transcript\":\"OK, recording this so I don't forget it tomorrow. Today was the crater day, Naurangoro, and it was honestly one of the best days of my life. Wildlife everywhere, right up close. Our driver guide today, not Richard from the office, the other guy, he said his name was Emmanuel, really knew his stuff, kept pointing things out before we even saw them. Anyway, at the rim, on the way out, there was a Maasai lady selling beaded bracelets, and I bought two for Athena Mari. And she wanted, I think it was $25 for both, or maybe it was $20, I honestly can't remember exactly. I paid in shillings, roughly $35,000 or so. Should have written it down right there. Also, Emmanuel mentioned there's sometimes an extra ranger ti\n...\n</persisted-output>","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_VS8SpQtfQDSL4mOWXxONhNyp","session_id":"a5bdaf5f-36c3-4bd0-a7f1-82b85daace12","uuid":"3424a950-ff66-4254-9d18-ced305cfa199","timestamp":"2026-07-16T09:08:54.975Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace app build completion"}
