 Emmanuel, really knew his stuff, kept pointing things out before we even saw them. Anyway, at the rim, on the way out, there was a Maasai lady selling beaded bracelets, and I bought two for Athena Mari. And she wanted, I think it was $25 for both, or maybe it was $20, I honestly can't remember exactly. I paid in shillings, roughly $35,000 or so. Should have written it down right there. Also, Emmanuel mentioned there's sometimes an extra ranger ti\n...\n</persisted-output>","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_VS8SpQtfQDSL4mOWXxONhNyp","session_id":"a5bdaf5f-36c3-4bd0-a7f1-82b85daace12","uuid":"f8312fe9-5a51-467d-b862-68171715acfc","timestamp":"2026-07-16T09:10:02.451Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace app build completion"}
