{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"aa22fd80460be852a","tool_use_id":"call_VS8SpQtfQDSL4mOWXxONhNyp","status":"completed","output_file":"/tmp/claude-1000/-home-vasilis-LMTHING-lmthing/a5bdaf5f-36c3-4bd0-a7f1-82b85daace12/tasks/aa22fd80460be852a.output","summary":"**Finding: genuine app-publish failure, not a `built` observability defect.**\n\n- Step 2 did author the live project: the persisted project contains `pages/_layout.tsx`, `pages/index.tsx`, and `api/dashboard/GET.ts`; tables and seeded rows are real. The absence of `writeProject*` yield kinds is expected: they are synchronous injected globals, not yield-router operations. Only calls such as `tasklist`, `delegate`, and `readDocument` produce trace yields.\n\n- `appManifest.built` is accurately reporting whether a compiled bundle exists, not whether source files exist. `pagesBuildInfo()` sets `built` solely from `.data/pages-dist/index.html`. At step 2 no build had been requested, so `false` is expected. The runner’s `snapshot()` only GETs the manifest; it does not build.\n\n- Step 3 proves the decisive failure. Its forced `POST /api/projects/tanzania-trip/app/build` returns 400:\n  `api/dashboard/GET.ts: missing export const name`.\n  The endpoint loader rejects the file before pages can compile, so no `pages-dist/index.html` is produced and `/app/.../` returns 404. Thus the host did not publish an openable app because the authored API is invalid.\n\n**Narrow root cause**\n\nThe `write_openable_app` tasklist prompt tells the model only to write a “handler that queries every table”; its template does not require the runtime’s mandatory endpoint-module shape. The model therefore emitted a Request/Response handler without `export const name` (and not the documented `ctx.db` API pattern).\n\nChange tasklist node **`write_openable_app`** in:\n\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/tasklists/build_live_project/03-write_openable_app.md`\n\nMake its API instruction/template require a complete module, specifically `export const name = 'dashboard'`, description, `Input`/`Output`, and `export default async function handler(_input, ctx) { await ctx.db.query(...) }`. This matches the existing canonical contract in:\n\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-appbuilder/knowledge/app_building/model/file-formats.md`\n- `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/cli/src/app/api/loader.ts` (`loadApiRoutes`).\n\n**Runner note:** `/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/run-yaml.mjs` `snapshot()` could add an `authored` field or explicitly label `built:false` as “not yet compiled,” but that is only clarity—not the cause.","usage":{"total_tokens":0,"tool_uses":59,"duration_ms":170865},"uuid":"0b62ccee-69af-4f78-bb2a-a5dc45df1e5c","session_id":"a5bdaf5f-36c3-4bd0-a7f1-82b85daace12"}
