ter model response.\n\n```typescript\ncurrentTask.resolve({\n  pages: ['index', '_layout'],\n  endpoints: ['dashboard/GET'],\n  ok: [\n    writeProjectApi('dashboard/GET', [\n      \"export const name = 'dashboard';\",\n      \"export const description = 'Read the project dashboard.';\",\n      \"export interface Input {}\",\n      \"export interface Output { data: Record<string, unknown[]> }\",\n      \"export default async function handler(_input: Input, ctx: { db: any }): Promise<Output> {\",\n      \"  return { data: {} };\",\n      \"}\",\n    ].join(\"\\\\n\")),\n    writeProjectPage('index', '<page that uses useApi on dashboard and renders actual rows>'),\n    writeProjectPage('_layout', '<persistent Chat dock layout>'),\n  ].every((write) => write.ok),\n});\n```","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":24,"oldLines":6,"newStart":24,"newLines":12,"lines":[" async handler that reads through `ctx.db`. The `name` is the same stable identifier the page passes"," to `useApi`; without it, the endpoint loader rejects the whole app before any page can compile."," ","+Every page source must use the project runtime and nothing else: import `useApi` and `Chat` only from","+`@app/runtime`; use ordinary React markup and design-token utility classes. Do NOT import","+`react-router`, `@agent-chat/react`, `@radix-ui/themes`, a relative `use-api` module, or any other","+package. Those packages are unavailable in a generated project and make every page fail to compile.","+The layout receives `children`; render them directly with the `Chat` dock, not an `Outlet`.","+"," Emit the API and both pages plus `currentTask.resolve(...)` in the same model response; values"," declared here must not be used by a later model response."," "]},{"oldStart":41,"oldLines":8,"newStart":47,"newLines":22,"lines":["       \"  return { data: {} };\",","       \"}\",","     ].join(\"\\\\n\")),","-    writeProjectPage('index', '<page that uses useApi on dashboard and renders actual rows>'),","-    writeProject